<headline>Heat Advisory issued July 31 at 2:39PM MDT until August 02 at 12:00AM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...HEAT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM NOON MONDAY TO MIDNIGHT MDT
MONDAY NIGHT...
* WHAT...Record hot temperatures of 95 to 105 at lower elevations
and low temperatures around 60 degrees.
* WHERE...Fergus, Blaine, Eastern Glacier, Hill, Liberty and Toole
Counties.
* WHEN...From Noon Monday to Midnight MDT Monday Night.
* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures may cause heat illnesses.</description>
<instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
